      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate task card describes a software engineering / reproducibility task (package installation and pytest execution), but the paper is a scientific research article describing the Biosynfoni fingerprint method and its validation.",
        "The paper validates Biosynfoni through scientific experiments (biosynthetic similarity estimation, natural product classification, chemical space visualization) rather than through automated test suites.",
        "No evidence in the paper of a public Python package repository, PyPI distribution, or CI/CD testing infrastructure.",
        "The paper mentions tools used (Python 3.13.1, RDKit 2024.09.4) but does not document how to install or test the Biosynfoni implementation as a standalone package."
