    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_002/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Biosynfoni's fingerprint contains the number of substructure matches returned for each of the 39 substructure keys... Biosynfoni can also be used like other fingerprints to visualise chemical space.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that Biosynfoni generates fingerprints with substructure counts (not strictly bit-vectors, but counted representations) for molecules. However, the paper does not explicitly specify CSV or NumPy format as output formats. The fingerprint is described as a counted array of 39 substructure keys, which is semantically similar but the specific output format (CSV/NumPy) is not documented in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01081-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Fingerprint file in CSV or NumPy format containing molecule identifiers and corresponding substructure bit-vector representations",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:21:04.566319+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstructing' the fingerprint computation, which is appropriate given the paper's methodological focus.",
        "The card does not mention key dependencies like RDKit, which is explicitly stated as a main tool in the paper ('We used Python [32] (v3.13.1) and the cheminformatic RDKit [21] package (v2024.09.4) as our main tools').",
        "The card's inclusion of pip and pytest suggests a software engineering/deployment context, but the paper is a research publication focused on the fingerprint algorithm itself, not on packaging or testing infrastructure."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
