    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Biosynfoni's fingerprint contains the number of substructure matches returned for each of the 39 substructure keys. We investigated Biosynfoni's applicability domain and its performance in biosynthetic similarity representation, chemical space visualisation, and natural product classification.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper analyzes fingerprint properties (substructure occurrence, co-occurrence, similarity patterns via Tanimoto) but does NOT analyze a 'deposited dataset' on Zenodo. The paper uses COCONUT, ChEBI, MetaCyc, and ZINC databases. No mention of a Zenodo deposit or dataset deposition in passages. The statistical analyses performed (occurrence heatmaps, pointwise mutual information, Tanimoto similarity) are present, but the scope is the paper's own analysis, not a separate deposited dataset.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01081-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What are the statistical properties of the biosynfoni fingerprint vectors in the deposited dataset, including bit-frequency distributions, sparsity characteristics, and pairwise similarity patterns?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:21:21.998109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_003/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The average atom coverage of 97% indicates Biosynfoni captures almost all of the atoms in the natural products' structures at least once with its 39 substructure keys (Online Figures A1 and A2). The average counts and count variation differ between substructure keys, with acetate pathway substructure keys showing the highest average counts and count variations (Fig. 1a, top)... We calculated Tanimoto similarity scores for compounds from biosynthetic reaction chains, for pairs with increasing numbers of metabolic reaction steps between them (Fig. 2b).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports substructure occurrence statistics (average counts, count variation) and Tanimoto similarity metrics, but these are presented as figures and online figures, not as a formal summary statistics table. Sparsity is not explicitly quantified as a metric in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01081-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Summary statistics table containing bit-frequency per position, sparsity, and pairwise Tanimoto similarity distribution metrics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:21:21.998109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_14822624__task_003/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Fig. 1a, top... Occurrences are shown as bottomless box plots due to the logarithmic scale of the y-axis... We visualised the similarity scores per n through kernel density estimate plots of the similarities (Fig. 2c).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper presents box plots of substructure occurrence (bit-frequency analogue) and kernel density estimate plots of Tanimoto similarity. However, sparsity is not explicitly visualized as a distribution plot in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-025-01081-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Distribution plots (histogram/density) visualizing bit-frequency, sparsity, and Tanimoto similarity across fingerprint vectors",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
